
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `cpan` yek rahe asan baraye gereftan, nasb kardan va modiriat module-haye Perl az shabake ast.  Ba `cpan`, shoma mitavanid module-haye jadid ezafe konid, module-haye mojood ra be rooz konid va hattaa module-ha ra hazf konid.  In yek abzar kheili mohem baraye karbarane Perl ast.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `cpan install Module::Name`  --> 📦 Nasb ya be-rooz-resani yek module khass.
    🔹 `cpan upgrade` --> ⬆️ Be-rooz-resani hameye module-hayi ke be rooz-resani niaz darand.
    🔹 `cpan uninstall Module::Name`  --> 🗑️ Hazf yek module az system.
    🔹 `cpan help` --> ❓ Namayesh rahnama baraye dastoor `cpan`.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ cpan install Mojolicious

    🔹 Nasb kardan framework Mojolicious Perl.

    $ cpan upgrade

    🔹 Be rooz resani hameye module haye Perl nasb shode.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ cpan install JSON::PP

    🔹 Dastoor bala module JSON::PP (Perl Pure) ra ke baraye kar ba format JSON ast, az CPAN download va nasb mikonad. Shoma badan mitavanid az in module dar barname haye Perl khod estefade konid.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `cpan` command provides an easy way to fetch, install, and manage Perl modules from the network.  With `cpan`, you can add new modules, update existing ones, and even remove modules.  It's a very important tool for Perl users.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `cpan install Module::Name`  --> 📦 Install or upgrade a specific module.
    🔹 `cpan upgrade` --> ⬆️ Upgrade all modules that have updates available.
    🔹 `cpan uninstall Module::Name`  --> 🗑️ Uninstall a module from the system.
    🔹 `cpan help` --> ❓ Show the help documentation for the `cpan` command.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ cpan install Mojolicious

    🔹 Install the Mojolicious Perl framework.

    $ cpan upgrade

    🔹 Upgrade all installed Perl modules to the latest versions.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ cpan install JSON::PP

    🔹 The command above downloads and installs the JSON::PP (Perl Pure) module, used for working with the JSON format, from CPAN. You can then use this module in your Perl programs.
